section.title: file documentation
section.DESCRIPTION:
This specification documents Major Version 1 of the Qualcomm technologies, Inc Messaging Interface (QMI) for WLAN Firmware Service (QMI_WLFW).
WLAN Host runs on APSS and WLAN Firmware runs on Modem. This service is used for downloading WLAN calibration data, WLAN board data and passing WLAN on/off status information from APSS to Modem. WLAN HOST plays the role of WLFW QMI client and WLAN Firmware plays the role of WLFW QMI server. There are two clients using this service. One is in user-space responsible for WLAN calibration data and WLAN board data. The other client is in kernel-space responsible for WLAN on/off information.

type.valuedescription: wfc_call_status buffer is not longer allowed with TWT config IDL update. We cannot use opaque buffer transfer between IMS and WLFW due to expanded QMI data structure below. This results in structure padding in decoded qmi data structures. For backward compatibility Host driver copies wfc_call_active value to it as per initial design.
WFC call status Values: - 0x00 -- Inactive - 0x01 -- Active
WFC call hold status Values: - 0x00 - At least once active WFC call - 0x01 - All WFC calls held
Is WFC call emergency Values: - 0x00 - No WFC emergency call active - 0x01 - Emergency WFC call active

WFC media quality - computed based on the media metrics and the end to end latency. Notified whenever there is a change in the quality or request received from the STA with change in the parameters which helps STA to evaluate the effectiveness of the change Values: - WFC_MEDIA_QUAL_NOT_AVAILABLE(0) - Default/quality not available - WFC_MEDIA_QUAL_BAD(1) - WFC_MEDIA_QUAL_GOOD(2) - WFC_MEDIA_QUAL_EXCELLENT(3)
